article.headline: Cornell 69, N.J.I.T. 58
article.story: ITHACA, N.Y. (AP) -- Ryan Wittman scored 17 points to lead Cornell in a 69-58 win over NJIT Sunday night. Graham Dow contributed 15 points for Cornell (7-7), while Louis Dale added 14. Marc Milbourne Swan scored 20 points for NJIT (2-13). Nesho Milosevic had 13 points and Clayton Barker scored 12. Cornell took the lead at 5-4 and never trailed again. Consecutive 3-pointers by Jason Mitchell and Dow to open the second half extended the lead to 36-26, two minutes into the half. NJIT never got within six points the rest of the way. Cornell finished with a 51.2 shooting percentage. The Big Red made 51 percent from the floor (22-43) and 50 percent from beyond the arc (8-16). NJIT was held to 40 percent shooting from the floor (18-45) and 11 percent from three-point range (1-11). Cornell outrebounded NJIT 32-21.
